03_13_2020 : 230 entries 09_13_2020 : 3954 entries

Additionally, the data from 03_13_2020 only includes the following characteristics: Province_State, Country_Region, Last Update, Confirmed, Deaths, Recovered, Latitude, Longitude. The data from 09_13_2020 has all of the previous data with the addition of the following characteristics: FIPS, Admin2, Active, Combined_Key, Incidence_Rate, and Case-Fatality_Ratio.

1.2. make a data frame with total counts for each country

report_03_13_2020 %>%

  summarize(total_Confirmed = sum(Confirmed), total_Deaths = sum(Deaths), total_recovered = sum(Recovered))

1.3. get counts for confirmed cases per U.S. state

report_03_13_2020 %>% 
  filter(Country_Region == "US") %>% 
  group_by(Province_State) %>% 
  summarize(total_Confirmed = sum(Confirmed)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_Confirmed))

2.1 make plots of the 10 countries with confirmed cases and deaths on 03_12_2020 (graph 1) and 09_12_2020 (graph 2)

report_03_12_2020 <-   read_csv(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_daily_reports/03-12-2020.csv")) %>% 
  rename(Country_Region = "Country/Region", Province_State = "Province/State")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `Province/State` = col_character(),
##   `Country/Region` = col_character(),
##   `Last Update` = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   Confirmed = col_double(),
##   Deaths = col_double(),
##   Recovered = col_double(),
##   Latitude = col_double(),
##   Longitude = col_double()
## )
report_09_12_2020 <- read_csv(url("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_daily_reports/09-12-2020.csv"))
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   FIPS = col_double(),
##   Admin2 = col_character(),
##   Province_State = col_character(),
##   Country_Region = col_character(),
##   Last_Update = col_datetime(format = ""),
##   Lat = col_double(),
##   Long_ = col_double(),
##   Confirmed = col_double(),
##   Deaths = col_double(),
##   Recovered = col_double(),
##   Active = col_double(),
##   Combined_Key = col_character(),
##   Incidence_Rate = col_double(),
##   `Case-Fatality_Ratio` = col_double()
## )
confirmed_cases_03_12_2020 <- 
  report_03_12_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarize(total_confirmed_cases = sum(Confirmed)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_confirmed_cases)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
deaths_03_12_2020 <- 
  report_03_12_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarize(total_deaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_deaths)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
confirmed_cases_09_12_2020 <- 
  report_09_12_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarize(total_confirmed_cases = sum(Confirmed)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_confirmed_cases)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
deaths_09_12_2020 <- 
  report_09_12_2020 %>% 
  group_by(Country_Region) %>% 
  summarize(total_deaths = sum(Deaths)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_deaths)) %>% 
  slice(1:10)
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
ggplot(data = confirmed_cases_03_12_2020, mapping = aes(x = Country_Region, y = total_confirmed_cases))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Country_Region))

ggplot(data = deaths_03_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_deaths))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Country_Region))

ggplot(data = confirmed_cases_09_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_confirmed_cases))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Country_Region))

ggplot(data = deaths_09_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_deaths))+
  geom_point(aes(color = Country_Region))

ggplot(data = confirmed_cases_03_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_confirmed_cases, fill = Country_Region))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") + 
  theme_minimal()

ggplot(data = deaths_03_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_deaths, fill = Country_Region))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") + 
  theme_minimal()

ggplot(data = confirmed_cases_09_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_confirmed_cases, fill = Country_Region))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") + 
  theme_minimal()

ggplot(data = deaths_09_12_2020, mapping = aes(x= Country_Region, y = total_deaths, fill = Country_Region))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") + 
  theme_minimal()
